\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1 On this day, Ludwig Boltzmann (
\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
1844-1906) was born. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Austrian}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosopher"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 philosopher}} whose greatest achievement was in the development of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 statistical mechanics}}, which explains and predicts how the properties of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atom"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 atoms}} (such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_mass"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mass}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electric_charge"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 charge}}, and structure) determine the physical properties of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matter"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 matter}} (such as viscosity, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermal_conductivity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 thermal conductivity}}, and diffusion). \
The Boltzamnn constant is named after him and is also due to him the formula describing the entropy as the logarithm of the possibility of occurrence of a thermodynamic macrostate.\cb1 \
